# vim:set ft=config:
#
# .trivyignore
#
# Every entry in this list should have its own, justified explanation for
# why we're skipping it.
#

# AVD-DS-0002 (HIGH): Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user as argument
# Skipped since we immediately pivot down from root in our startup script,
# and starting as root allows us to sanity check more configuration.
AVD-DS-0002
DS-0002

# AVD-DS-0029 (HIGH): '--no-install-recommends' flag is missed
# I disagree that this is a vulnerability. Additionally, Trivy is not
# intelligent about multi-stage builds where we might *want* the packages
# recommended by APT.
AVD-DS-0029
DS-0029
